# Phase 37: Vercel Deployment & Complete UI Redesign

## Problem Statement
Current UI scored **3/10 beauty, 2/10 modern usability** by the product owner. The design lacks:
- Visual hierarchy and breathing room
- Modern card aesthetics (inconsistent borders, harsh Obsidian blocks)
- Mobile-first layout (BottomNav is functional but not polished)
- Engaging hero section and onboarding flow
- Clean typography scale (Bebas Neue everywhere looks typewriter-heavy)

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The new design is a **complete visual overhaul** — different color palette, typography, card style, and navigation pattern. The backend/API routes remain unchanged. Please review the design direction below and approve before execution.

> [!WARNING]  
> The Cloudflare R2 env vars **must be added to Vercel** as secrets — they are in [.env.local](file:///C:/GOLive/.env.local) which is gitignored. You'll need to paste them via the Vercel dashboard or CLI after deployment. Steps are included below.

